cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper is about face recognition systems and their bias against demographic sub-groups. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel fair score normalization approach, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another likely category. The paper also mentions the overall performance boost achieved by the proposed approach, indicating that it involves optimization techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also mentions the use of individual fairness, which is a concept in ethics and philosophy, indicating that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on publicly available datasets, indicating that cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category.
